    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Hey there, thanks for the question :)\r\n\r\nWe use [debug](https://www.npmjs.com/package/debug) for our ts logging so you can use `env DEBUG=\"your-logger-name-here\" yarn test ...` to look at things logged in js (at the top of our testfiles, you should see a `getLogger(\"logger-name\")`.  To debug internal EVM traces is a little more difficult -- one option is to use [debug_traceTransaction](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Management-APIs#debug_tracetransaction) by adding a line to the test which says `const aTrace = ethers.provider.send('debug_traceTransaction', [<desired arguments>])`.\r\n\r\nHope this helps!",
